& =\frac{n}{2}+\frac{n}{4}=\frac{n^{2}}{4}
\end{aligned}
$$

于是

$$
\begin{aligned}
f(n) & =\frac{1}{n+34+\frac{64}{n}}=\frac{1}{\frac{n^{2}}{4}+34+\frac{64}{n}} \\
& =\frac{4}{n^{2}+34 n+64} \\
